              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH",
                "SISD",
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "The experimental setup used a hybrid",
                "ion chamber/silicon detector system with 5 x 5 cm",
                "active area, located 15.8 cm behind the secondary",
                "target, with its center blocked by a 1 cm2 square",
                "beam stopper. The silicon double surface strip",
                "detector (DSSD) with a segmentation of 16 x 16",
                "strips and a thickness of 491 mu-m was backed up by",
                "a second 5 x 5 cm unsegmented detector, which served",
                "as a veto against high-energy protons punching through",
                "the DSSD."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MCPLT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A microchannel plate detector located 2.7 m",
                "upstream of the final target position was used to",
                "suppress the majority of beam contaminants off-line",
                "through a time-of-flight measurement,"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Inverse kinematics proton-transfer reaction",
                "25Al(d,n)26Si with 25Al beam and CD2 target was used",
                "to populate states of 26Si."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Time of flight allowed to achieve a beam purity",
                "of 67% in off line analysis."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The primary beam of 24Mg bombarded a gas-cell target",
                "containing D2 gas, creating the desired 25Al particles",
                "through the inverse kinematics 24Mg(d,n)25Al reaction.",
                "The resulting beam of 25Al at energy of 91.5 MeV  was",
                "selected to a purity of 20% using RESOLUT - a mass",
                "spectrometer with active beam cooling."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Resonance parameters of 26Si were determined using",
                "inverse kinematics reaction d(25Al,n)26Si"
              ]
            }
          ],
